main event: Rocket or missile launch observed by a witness. Visual sightings came in rapidly, object appeared to be traveling at extremely high speed and at an extremely high altitude.
interesting points: The object was burning brightly and then disappeared from view after about 3 minutes.
The sighting was verified as a missile launch by SAFOS.
There were two explosions noticed during the sighting.
The object crossed the witness's zenith and disappeared in the direction of bearing 242 degrees.
Another sighting described the object separating into two lighted objects and appearing to fire another stage.
sighted object: One or more high-speed, high-altitude objects
witnesses: Air Force Colonel, Frying Pan Lightship, and other unspecified witnesses
photographs: No photographs included in the report
